== <span data-segmentid="425" class="cx-segment">音乐风格</span> ==
<span data-segmentid="426" class="cx-segment">该乐队第一张专辑结合了[[前衛金屬|前卫金属]]和[[太空摇滚|太空摇滚]]的影响以及[[电子乐|电子乐]]的元素，运用了[[Programming_(music)|电子制作]]和合成器。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Rock Implosion|last=Uhelszki|first=Jaan|date=September 2002|journal=Alternative Press|issue=170|page=79}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.melodic.net/?page=review&id=529|title=30 Seconds to Mars|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Wippsson|first=Johan|work=Melodic|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923034022/http://www.melodic.net/?page=review&id=529|archivedate=2013-09-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> </span><span data-segmentid="431" class="cx-segment">''[[Blender_(magazine)|Blender]]杂志的''Ryan Rayhill认为这张专辑是一种“具有思想高度史诗般效果的[[Rock_opera|太空歌剧]]与[[匆促樂團|匆促乐团]]式的前卫摇滚相适应的产物（high-minded space opera of epic scope befitting prog-rock prototypes Rush）”，并写道，30秒上火星“带着一张听起来像是[[工具乐队|工具乐队]]来表演''[[月之暗面|月之暗面]]''</span>（指平克·弗洛伊德在1973年发布的专辑）一样的同名处女作横空出世（emerged with an eponymous debut that sounds like Tool on ''The Dark Side of the Moon）''<span data-segmentid="431" class="cx-segment">”。<ref name="blender">{{Cite journal|title=30 Seconds to Mars|last=Rayhill|first=Ryan|date=September 2002|journal=Blender|issue=9|page=142}}</ref></span><span data-segmentid="462" class="cx-segment">尽管乐队首张[[概念專輯|概念专辑]]的歌词重点放在了人的斗争和自我决断， ''《美丽的谎言》''</span>的歌词则<span data-segmentid="462" class="cx-segment">是更加地私人化，且在音乐上引入了[[嘶吼唱腔|嘶吼唱腔]]。<ref name="nbcu2" /> </span><span data-segmentid="465" class="cx-segment">这一</span><span data-segmentid="462" class="cx-segment">转</span><span data-segmentid="465" class="cx-segment">变在整张专辑中都得到了体现，反映了乐队成员在专辑创作过程中所经历的个人层面和艺术层面上的变化。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://shoutweb.com/interviews/30secondstomars0905.phtml|title=30 Seconds To Mars: A Savory Reality|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Campagna|first=Cathy A.|publisher=Shoutweb.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110315210140/http://shoutweb.com/interviews/30secondstomars0905.phtml|archivedate=2011-03-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 这张</span><span data-segmentid="466" class="cx-segment">专辑</span><span data-segmentid="465" class="cx-segment">通过融合来自前卫摇滚、硬核摇滚</span><span data-segmentid="466" class="cx-segment">和[[Emo|情绪硬核]]的元素，拓宽了乐队的声音风格。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=A 30 Seconds Love Affair|last=Palm|first=Matthew J.|date=November 5, 2006|journal=Orlando Sentinel|page=E9}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/music/live_reviews/article2482314.ece|title=30 Seconds to Mars|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Verrico|date=September 19, 2007|first=Lisa|work=[[The_Times|The Times]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090519093252/http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/music/live_reviews/article2482314.ece|archivedate=2009-05-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/30-seconds-to-mars/music/30secondstomarsx12x03x07|title=A Beautiful Lie|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Rea|first=Mike|publisher=[[Contactmusic.com|Contactmusic.com]]|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818163959/https://www.contactmusic.com/30-seconds-to-mars/music/30secondstomarsx12x03x07|dead-url=no}}</ref></span> <span data-segmentid="468" class="cx-segment">这种</span><span data-segmentid="466" class="cx-segment">另类</span><span data-segmentid="468" class="cx-segment">摇滚风格被拿来与[[治疗乐队|治疗乐队]]、[[U2樂團|U2乐团]]以及[[碎南瓜乐队|碎南瓜乐队]]的音乐相比较。<ref name="nbcu2"/></span>

<span data-segmentid="472" class="cx-segment">他们的第三张专辑''《全面开战》''</span>被认为拥有“极具前卫<span data-segmentid="472" class="cx-segment">摇滚风格的声音和非常抓耳的旋律”，从实验性的平克·弗洛伊德到旋律化的[[M83_(band)|M83]]中获取灵感。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aolradioblog.com/2009/12/08/30-seconds-to-mars-this-is-war/|title=30 Seconds to Mars 'This Is War'|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Anderson|date=December 8, 2009|first=Sara D.|publisher=[[AOL_Radio|AOL Radio]]|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65jmT7D8k?url=http://www.aolradioblog.com/2009/12/08/30-seconds-to-mars-this-is-war/|archive-date=2012-02-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref></span> <span data-segmentid="474" class="cx-segment">''[[滾石_(雜誌)|滚石]]''</span>杂志的Chris Harris <span data-segmentid="474" class="cx-segment">认为，这是经过乐队成员们的个人抗争与和厂牌之间法律纠纷打造的“一张充满野心[[Experimental_rock|实验摇滚]]作品集”<ref name="survival2"/> 网站</span><span data-segmentid="477" class="cx-segment">[[Allmusic|AllMusic]]的Stephen Thomas Erlewine认可了在这张专辑的整体风格上，乐队融合[[Electronic_rock|电子摇滚]]、[[重金属音乐|重金属]]和前卫摇滚的成果。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/this-is-war-mw0001792357|title=This Is War|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Erlewine|first=Stephen Thomas|publisher=AllMusic. All Media Network|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020091845/https://www.allmusic.com/album/this-is-war-mw0001792357|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>

<span data-segmentid="481" class="cx-segment">在''《爱 欲 信 + 梦》''</span>中<span data-segmentid="481" class="cx-segment">''，''</span>乐队尝试运用不同的乐器，并吸收了<span data-segmentid="481" class="cx-segment">更广泛的、更多样化的音乐风格。<ref name="llfd2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1707774/thirty-seconds-to-mars-love-lust-faith-dreams.jhtml|title=Thirty Seconds To Mars Set To 'Unleash The Beast' On Love Lust Faith + Dreams|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Montgomery|date=May 21, 2013|first=James|publisher=MTV News. Viacom Media Networks|archive-date=2014-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314023029/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1707774/thirty-seconds-to-mars-love-lust-faith-dreams.jhtml|dead-url=no}}</ref></span><span data-segmentid="482" class="cx-segment">这张专辑融合了实验性的乐器演奏，</span><span data-segmentid="481" class="cx-segment">也采用了</span><span data-segmentid="482" class="cx-segment">[[前衛搖滾|前卫摇滚]]和电子音乐元素，引入了一种充满飘渺音效的、极简的演奏方式。<ref name="llfd2" /><ref>{{Cite journal|title=To Infinity & Beyond|last=Sayce|first=Rob|date=July 2013|journal=Rock Sound|page=62}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1563061/thirty-seconds-to-mars-love-lust-faith-dreams-track-by-track-review|title=Thirty Seconds To Mars, 'Love Lust Faith + Dreams': Track-By-Track Review|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Zemler|date=May 21, 2013|first=Emily|work=Billboard|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922133558/https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1563061/thirty-seconds-to-mars-love-lust-faith-dreams-track-by-track-review|dead-url=no}}</ref></span> <span data-segmentid="484" class="cx-segment">这张专辑拥有着''全面开战''式的概念专辑形式，却扩大了范畴，围绕着它名称所指代的主题而发展演化。<ref name="llfd2" /></span>

== 社会活动 ==
<span data-segmentid="486" class="cx-segment">30秒上火星建立了一个名为abeautifullie.org的网站，提供有关环境问题和参与环保活动的信息及资讯。<ref name="environment">{{Cite web|url=http://www.melodic.net/?page=news&id=9861|title=Jared Leto Is Back With A New Video And Global Cause|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Wippsson|date=March 8, 2008|first=Johan|work=Melodic|archive-date=2013-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923010902/http://www.melodic.net/?page=news&id=9861|dead-url=no}}</ref> </span><span data-segmentid="487" class="cx-segment">人们通过该网站捐款，以支持[[Natural_Resources_Defense_Council|自然资源保护委员会]]的工作。<ref name="environment" /> </span><span data-segmentid="489" class="cx-segment">2006年，杰瑞德·莱托</span><span data-segmentid="487" class="cx-segment">为电台97X汇编的现场表演专辑</span><span data-segmentid="489" class="cx-segment">''[[The_97X_Green_Room:_Volume_2|《The 97X Green Room: Volume 2》]]''</span>创作了专辑封面。这张专辑包含了一首30秒上<span data-segmentid="489" class="cx-segment">火星的歌曲，它的销售获益被用以支持[[大自然保护协会|大自然保护协会]]。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://97xonline.com/greenroom/volume2.html|title=97X Green Room: Volume 2|accessdate=July 26, 2011|publisher=[[WSUN_(FM)|97x]]. [[Cox_Enterprises|Cox Media Group]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090607115103/http://97xonline.com/greenroom/volume2.html|archivedate=2009-06-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref></span> <span data-segmentid="492" class="cx-segment">在巡演[[Welcome_to_the_Universe_Tour|Welcome ro the Universe Tour]]期间，该乐队尽力采取措施，最大限度地减少了燃料消耗量以抵消巡演所产生的对环境的影响。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soundspike.com/story2/10718/30-seconds-to-mars-goes-green-on-mtv2-tour/|title=30 Seconds to Mars goes green on MTV2 tour|accessdate=May 12, 2015|author=Zahlaway|date=September 15, 2006|first=Jon|publisher=[[SoundSpike|SoundSpike]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923005905/http://www.soundspike.com/story2/10718/30-seconds-to-mars-goes-green-on-mtv2-tour/|archivedate=2013-09-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref></span>

<span data-segmentid="494" class="cx-segment">2008年6月，乐队参与[[國際仁人家園|国际仁人家园]]组织的工作，帮助修复了一处房屋以相应大洛杉矶地区的"A Brush With Kindness"项目。<ref name="habitat">{{Cite web|url=http://www.abeautifullie.org/news.aspx?DiaryID=924|title=30 Seconds To Mars And Hollywood For Habitat For Humanity Unite For One-Of-A-Kind Build|accessdate=September 12, 2013|date=June 30, 2008|publisher=abeautifullie.org|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005065344/http://abeautifullie.org/news.aspx?DiaryID=924|archivedate=2011-10-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 除此之外</span><span data-segmentid="496" class="cx-segment">，乐队组织了一次拍卖，歌迷可以通过拍卖得到与他们一起参与志愿建造的机会。 </span><span data-segmentid="497" class="cx-segment">不到一星期的时间，他们征集到六个额外的工人和超过10 000美元的款项，用以支持国际仁人家园的额外项目。<ref name="habitat" />30秒上</span><span data-segmentid="498" class="cx-segment">火星的歌迷，也就是所谓的Echelon，创建了数个慈善组织和慈善项目，目的是支持</span><span data-segmentid="497" class="cx-segment">各种</span><span data-segmentid="498" class="cx-segment">慈善和人道主义</span><span data-segmentid="497" class="cx-segment">机构的工作</span><span data-segmentid="498" class="cx-segment">。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://act.mtv.com/posts/international-echelon-conference/|title=30 Seconds To Mars Fans Give Back at International Echelon Conference|accessdate=September 10, 2013|author=Frucht|date=May 3, 2012|first=Becca|publisher=[[MTV_Act|MTV Act]]. Viacom Media Networks|archive-date=2012-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120726224001/http://act.mtv.com/posts/international-echelon-conference/|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>

<span data-segmentid="499" class="cx-segment">在[[2010年海地地震|2010年海地地震]]后，30秒上火星通过一场慈善拍卖为海地赈灾筹得了善款100 100美元。<ref name="haiti">{{Cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/3767-30-seconds-to-mars-raises-100100-for-haiti|title=30 Seconds To Mars Raises $100,100 For Haiti|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Sally|date=January 29, 2010|first=Catrina K.|publisher=Look to the Stars|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818151420/https://www.looktothestars.org/news/3767-30-seconds-to-mars-raises-100100-for-haiti|dead-url=no}}</ref>该</span><span data-segmentid="501" class="cx-segment">乐队还通过Echelon项目House for Haiti及电视特典Hope For Haiti Now</span><span data-segmentid="499" class="cx-segment">为海地人民提供支持</span><span data-segmentid="501" class="cx-segment">。<ref name="haiti" /> 乐队</span><span data-segmentid="502" class="cx-segment">拍卖了一定数量的物品筹集善款，以支持红十字会救助[[2011年日本東北地方太平洋近海地震|2011年日本3·11大地震]]中的受灾群众。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hangout.altsounds.com/news/128215-artists-songwriters-emi-family-unite-japan.html|title=Artists and Songwriters from the EMI Family Unite for Japan|accessdate=September 12, 2013|author=Stovin|date=April 5, 2011|first=Jack|publisher=AltSounds|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830022751/http://hangout.altsounds.com/news/128215-artists-songwriters-emi-family-unite-japan.html|archivedate=2011-08-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 在乐队巡演</span><span data-segmentid="504" class="cx-segment">[[Carnivores_Tour|Carnivores Tour]]售出的每一张演出门票都包含向[[Music_for_Relief|Music for Relief]]组织捐出的一美元，以支持救灾以及环境的保护和恢复项目。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/linkin-park-thirty-seconds-to-mars-afi-join-forces-on-carnivores-tour-one-dollar-per-1935272.htm|title=Linkin Park, Thirty Seconds to Mars and AFI Join Forces on Carnivores Tour; One Dollar per Ticket to Benefit Music for Relief|accessdate=September 28, 2014|author=Britton|date=August 5, 2014|first=Kymm|publisher=[[Marketwired|Marketwired]]|archive-date=2018-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704155558/http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/linkin-park-thirty-seconds-to-mars-afi-join-forces-on-carnivores-tour-one-dollar-per-1935272.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>
